  <li>
    <p>“<b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="Come to that"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(实际上/事实上)</code></b>, we have no police nowadays; no crimes past or present, no more criminals—only <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="condemned men"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(被判了刑的人)</code></b> hoping for the most capricious of pardons; and among these are the police themselves.”</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“In short, this epidemic has <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="done him proud"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(做令自己风光或骄傲的事，意译为鼠疫是他感到风光)</code></b>. Of a lonely man who hated loneliness it has made an accomplice. Yes, ‘accomplice’ is the word that fits, and doesn’t he relish his complicity!</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“<b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="Prate away - (prate - to talk long and idly)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(尽管说吧)</code></b>, my friends—but I had it first!”</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“Of course I see his point, and I understand how <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="\ kən-ˈjē-nē-əl , -ˈjēn-yəl \ PLEASANT"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">congenial</code></b> our present mode of life must be to him. How could he fail to recognize <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="at every turn"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(处处/事事/每次)</code></b> reactions that were his; the efforts everyone makes to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="keep on the right side of other people"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(避免得罪其他人/争取其他人的好感)</code></b>; the obligingness sometimes shown in helping someone who has lost his way, and the ill humor shown at other times…</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“And I should say that when tempted to visit a brothel he refrains; it might give him a bad name and be <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="held up against him - (hold something against somebody - 因...对某人抱有成见)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(会对他不利)</code></b> one day.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“And a moment later he added: ‘Say what you like, Tarrou, but let me tell you this: the one way of making people <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="hang together"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(相互支持/互相帮助/同心协力)</code></b> is to give ’em <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="a spell of"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(一段短暂时间/一阵)</code></b> plague. You’ve only got to look around you.’</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>He is happily at one with all around him, with their superstitions, their groundless panics, the susceptibilities of people whose nerves are always <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="on the stretch"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(处于紧张状态)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>…and, lastly, with their <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="\ ˈfrād \ worn or shredded at the ends or edges"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">frayed</code></b>, irritable sensibility that <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="takes offense at"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(对...生气/因...见怪)</code></b> trifling <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="an inadvertent omission or error 小疏忽/小差错"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">oversights</code></b> and brings tears to their eyes over the loss of a trouser-button.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>‘In fact, one might go farther; have you ever heard of a man with cancer being killed in an <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="auto smash"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(车祸)</code></b>?’ This theory, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="for what it’s worth"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(无论如何/无论怎么样)</code></b>, keeps Cottard cheerful.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>This may explain why the entries in Tarrou’s diary of this period tend to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="converge on"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(集中于)</code></b> Cottard’s personality.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>It is obvious that Tarrou was attempting to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="give a full-length picture of"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(给...全面的描述)</code></b> the man and noted all his reactions and reflections, whether as conveyed to him by Cottard or interpreted by himself.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>For Cottard <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="was anything but upset"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(完全没因为...不安)</code></b> by <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="the turn events were taking"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(事情的转变)</code></b>. Sometimes in Tarrou’s company he voiced his true feelings in remarks of this order: “Getting worse every day, isn’t it? Well, anyhow, everyone’s in the same boat.”</p>
